title: France Current Account
description: France recorded a Current Account deficit of 7336 EUR Million in September of 2022. Current Account in France averaged -38.85 EUR Million from 1993 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 4784 EUR Million in August of 1998 and a record low of -7966 EUR Million in June of 2020. Current Account is the sum of the balance of trade (exports minus imports of goods and services), net factor income (such as interest and dividends) and net transfer payments (such as foreign aid). This page provides - France Current Account - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Banque de France
